Package: colorscience
Type: Package
Title: Color Science Methods and Data
Version: 1.0.6
Encoding: UTF-8
Maintainer: Paul Murrell <paul@stat.auckland.ac.nz>
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Jose", family = "Gama", role = c("aut","cre"),email = "rxprtgama@gmail.com"), person(given = "Paul", family = "Murrell", role = c("ctb"), email = "paul@stat.auckland.ac.nz"))
Description: Methods and data for color science - color conversions by observer,
        illuminant and gamma. Color matching functions and chromaticity diagrams.
        Color indices, color differences and spectral data conversion/analysis.
        This is a fork made off the CRAN version 1.0.4.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Depends: R (>= 2.10), Hmisc, munsellinterpol, pracma, sp
Enhances: png
LazyData: yes
Author: Jose Gama [aut, cre]
Repository: CRAN
NeedsCompilation: no
